              <p>Ayurveda, the traditional Indian medicinal system remains as the most ancient living traditions with sound philosophical and experimental basis.  “Ayurveda” is originated from the Sanskrit words “Ayur” (life) and “Veda” (science of knowledge).  It is the science of life with a holistic approach to health and personalized medicine. It is known to be a complete medical system that comprises physical, psychological, philosophical, ethical, and spiritual health. Ayurveda, is also called as self-healing science. It uses herbal medicines to coordinate and maintain the balance of body, mind, and spirit. This balance is believed to lead to health and happiness.</p>
              <p>Yoga is a 5000-year-old Indian science. There are various types of yoga, each having its own distinct emphasis regarding the relative content of physical postures and exercises (asanas), breathing techniques (pranayama), deep relaxation, and meditation practices. Yoga asanas cultivate awareness and ultimately more profound states of consciousness. The application of yoga as a therapeutic intervention, results in curing of numerous complicated conditions. Yoga asanas results in increase in patient’s physical flexibility, coordination, and strength. Breathing practices and meditation may calm and focus the mind to develop greater awareness and diminish anxiety, and thus result in higher quality of life. Other beneficial effects might involve reduction of distress, blood pressure, and improves resilience, mood, and metabolic regulation. Yoga uniquely embraces all realms of human wellness. It is evident that yoga therapy triggers multiple complex reactions in the body, resulting in cumulative effects on the muscles, internal organ systems, and glands and ultimately leading to enhanced quality of life. </p>
              <p>Ayuryoga Gurukulam blends Ayurveda and Yoga in a unique way to explore the benefits of both the systems for the wellbeing of human system. It also address and offers cure for many of the chronic physical and mental diseases, which otherwise appear as an incurable ailment. The institution offers a few unique courses which employ both Ayurveda and Yoga to cure some major chronic ailments. This will enable the participant to diagnose and handle the ailment in a Yogic and Ayurvedic way. </p>
              <p>Rejuvenation programs are offered to reestablish the vibrancy of each individual’s system depending on the existing condition. Beauty care program and Ayurvedic food preparations are also taught. Ayurveda Dinacharya programs is another attraction which enable the participant to analyze the fundamental make of each and every human being based on Tri doshas and Tri gunas so that, he may propose curative measure in daily routine to bring balance among them; which result in ultimate well being of the individual including health. Panchakarma is one of the ancient and a powerful tool in ayurveda utilized to maintain equilibrium of body or doshas and cure chronic diseases by detoxification of human system. Panchakarma therapies are also included along with Ayuryoga Rejuvenation therapy.</p>
              <p>The courses and programs were offered in a vibrant and positive atmosphere which is prevailed by the enchanting compassion and grace of Great Indian master and realized Yogi “Sree Narayana Guru”. This makes the event a spiritually fulfilling experience. </p>
